Package actions

Class ElementFinder

java.lang.Object
actions.ElementFinder
public class ElementFinder extends Object
The ElementFinder class is responsible for mapping human-readable locator types to their corresponding internal locator types. It provides a mapping of strings to LocatorType enum values for easy lookup. The class also stores a static reference to the Driver instance to be used for locating elements.

      public SikuliElement getSikuliElement​(String locatorType, String parameter1, String parameter2, long duration)
      Retrieves the SikuliElement representing the UI element using the given locator type and parameters, within the specified duration.
      Parameters:
      locatorType - The type of locator to use for finding the UI element (e.g., "NAME", "ID", "TEXT", etc.).
      parameter1 - The first parameter required for the locator (e.g., the name, ID, or text to search for).
      parameter2 - The second parameter (if applicable) required for the locator (e.g., partial text or value).
      duration - The maximum duration, in seconds, to wait for the UI element to be found.
      Returns:
      The SikuliElement representing the UI element if found, or null if the element is not found within the specified duration.

    • getElement

      public <T extends SikuliElement> T getElement​(String locatorType, String parameter1, String parameter2, long duration)
      Retrieves a UiElement or SikuliElement based on the provided locator type, parameters, and duration.
      Type Parameters:
      T - The type of element to retrieve, which can be either SikuliElement or UIElement.
      Parameters:
      locatorType - The type of locator to use for finding the element (e.g., "NAME", "ID", "TEXT", "IMAGE", "LOCATION", "OCR").
      parameter1 - The first parameter for locating the element, which can be the control type, search area image, or coordinate-X value.
      parameter2 - The second parameter for locating the element, which can be the control value, search element image, or coordinate-Y value.
      duration - The maximum duration, in seconds, to wait for the element to be found.
      Returns:
      The retrieved UiElement or SikuliElement if found, or null if the element is not found or an exception occurs during retrieval.

    • vanish

      public boolean vanish​(String locatorType, String parameter1, String parameter2, long duration)
      Waits for the element specified by the locator type and parameters to vanish from the screen within the given duration. The method checks for the element's presence repeatedly until it vanishes or the specified duration is exceeded.
      Parameters:
      locatorType - The type of locator to use for finding the element (e.g., "NAME", "ID", "TEXT", "IMAGE", "LOCATION", "OCR").
      parameter1 - The first parameter for locating the element, which can be the control type, search area image, or coordinate-X value.
      parameter2 - The second parameter for locating the element, which can be the control value, search element image, or coordinate-Y value.
      duration - The maximum duration, in seconds, to wait for the element to vanish.
      Returns:
      True if the element vanishes within the specified duration, false otherwise.

    • display

      public boolean display​(String locatorType, String parameter1, String parameter2, long duration)
      Waits for the element specified by the locator type and parameters to be displayed on the screen within the given duration. The method checks for the element's presence and visibility repeatedly until it is displayed or the specified duration is exceeded.
      Parameters:
      locatorType - The type of locator to use for finding the element (e.g., "NAME", "ID", "TEXT", "IMAGE", "LOCATION", "OCR").
      parameter1 - The first parameter for locating the element, which can be the control type, search area image, or coordinate-X value.
      parameter2 - The second parameter for locating the element, which can be the control value, search element image, or coordinate-Y value.
      duration - The maximum duration, in seconds, to wait for the element to be displayed.
      Returns:
      True if the element is displayed within the specified duration, false otherwise.

    • waitToEnable

      public boolean waitToEnable​(String locatorType, String controlType, String value, long duration)
      Waits for the specified element to become enabled within the given duration. The method checks for the element's presence and whether it is enabled repeatedly until it is enabled or the specified duration is exceeded.
      Parameters:
      locatorType - The type of locator to use for finding the element (e.g., "NAME", "ID", "TEXT").
      controlType - The type of the control to use for locating the element (e.g., "BUTTON", "TEXTBOX").
      value - The value of the element, such as the control value or text to search for.
      duration - The maximum duration, in seconds, to wait for the element to become enabled.
      Returns:
      True if the element becomes enabled within the specified duration, false otherwise.
